pageContext.claim: “Sixty-six thousand votes, each one of these is far more than we need. Sixty-six thousand votes in Georgia were cast by individuals under the legal voting age.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is citing claims made by Bryan Geels, a certified public accountant who owns a data analytics firm,. But Georgia election officials say this is wrong. “The actual number is zero,” Georgia elections official Gabriel Sterling told reporters, “and the reason we know that is because the dates are on the voter registration. There are four cases — four — where people requested their absentee ballot before they turned 18, but they turned 18 by Election Day. That means that is a legally cast ballot.”
